# batch multiple actions in a single addActions call to minimize round trips

The `addActions` MCP tool accepts an array of actions. Instead of making separate calls for each operation, batch them:

```typescript
// ✅ One call with multiple actions
addActions({
  documentId: "...",
  actions: [
    { type: "SET_MODEL_NAME", scope: "global", input: { name: "Invoice" } },
    { type: "SET_MODEL_DESCRIPTION", scope: "global", input: { description: "..." } },
    { type: "ADD_MODULE", scope: "global", input: { id: "...", name: "header" } },
  ]
});

// ❌ Three separate calls — slower and more failure-prone
```

Batching reduces network overhead and ensures related changes are applied atomically. If one action in a batch fails, the error is visible without having lost context from intermediate calls.

